('hav-dhmgdfpf063', 'DHMGDFPF063', 'Havells MCB FP D Curve', 'Havells', 'Switchgear', 'Circuit Breaker · Execution pole Four Pole (FP) · Type D Curve · Rating 63 A', 4379, 2575, 'pc', 'https://havells.com/media/catalog/product/cache/74c1057f7991b4edb2bc7bdaa94de933/import/Switchgear/DHMGDFPF063.jpg', null, 'DHMGDFPF063', null, '{"source":"havells.com","description":"63 A","key_features":["Application : Suitable for protection against overload & short circuit for high inrush current loads.","Rating : 0.5 A to 63 A","Specification : IS/IEC 60898-1","Note: Product images are for illustrative purposes and may differ from the actual product"],"features":[{"title":"Safety Terminals","body":"To avoid improper cable termination, the safety terminals guide the cable towards the cage terminal for systematic termination"},{"title":"Bi Stable Clip","body":"Every device is provided with a dual position DIN rail clip, so it becomes much easier to change a device from a device bank connected to a bus-bar, without disturbing the existing wiring"},{"title":"Large Cable Terminals","body":"Suitable for copper and aluminum cables, these terminals are compatible with cables upto 35 mm 2 cross section area"},{"title":"Cooler Operation","body":"Grooves provided on outer body, so that when individual poles are placed adjacent to each other in a distribution board it forms a very effective channel for better air circulation, resulting into a cooler operation"},{"title":"Precise hammer action","body":"A hammer directly connectd to the plunger strikes the moving contact arm with a force proportional to the peak current there by forcibly separating the moving contact from the fixed contact much before the latch mechanism operates.this further reduces the opening time of the circuit breaker."},{"title":"Low power consumption","body":"Consumes less power, thus cost effective and energy saving."},{"title":"13 Plates Arc Chute for effective arc quenching","body":"The arc extinguishing device comprises of 13 plates arc chute. The arc under the influence of the magnetic field and arc guide is moved into th arc chute where it is rapidly split and quenched."},{"title":"Trip free mechanism","body":"A circuit-breaker, the moving contacts of which return to and remain in the open position when the automatic opening operation is initiated after the initiation of the closing operation, even if the closing command is maintained."}],"specs":{"Manufactured By":"Havells India Ltd.","Country Of Origin":"India","Execution pole":"Four Pole (FP)","Type":"D Curve","Rating":"63 A","Net Contents":"1 N Main Unit","Net Quantity":"1 N","Product range":"Circuit Breaker"}}'::jsonb, true),
